Urges Nigerians To Uphold Justice, Peace At Ramadan, Easter ABUJA – President of the Nigeria Basketball Federation NBBF, Igoche Mark, has vowed to give a further boost to the new discipline of the dunking game, Para Basketball and give Players the opportunity to showcase their talents in the game. Mark disclosed the resolve of the federation stating that a Para Basketball League will be part of the calendar of the Federation in 2023. The NBBF President made the promise earlier in the week after watching a Para Basketball game at the ongoing National Para Games holding at the Package B, MKO Abiola Stadium Abuja. Mark said his board has promised to develop the slam and dunk, starting from the grassroots with an all-inclusive package that will include all players, irrespective of their physical challenge. “We have promised basketball stakeholders including players, officials and administrators that the main goal of our board is grassroots development, a development that will be all-inclusive, irrespective of the physical challenge anyone might be going through. “The NBBF will soon announce the commencement of a Para Basketball League in 2023. I commend the Ministry for hosting the National Para Games, and I pray this will continue.” Meanwhile, Igoche Mark has congratulated Nigerian Christians on this year’s Easter celebration. POLL Mark, in his Easter message, said the season was a signal of the importance of sacrifice in our daily lives while noting the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ was all about love, sharing and laying down of a precious seed that has birthed salvation. “I join our Christian brothers and sisters to celebrate this year’s Easter, especially our Basketball Stakeholders. Easter celebration is unique because it signals the importance of sacrifice in our daily lives. The death, burial and resurrection of Jesus Christ were all about love, sharing and laying down of his precious life or seed has birthed salvation,” Mark stated in his message.